  "text": "where the product is over the four TRIM in T 2 , pf denotes the pfaffian defined for antisymmetric matrices and det w(k) is defined as above. Since det w(k)/pf w(k) squares to 1, the right hand side of (II.8) is ±1. It is independent of the global sign ambiguity in the definition of det w(k) and may be shown [CITATION_1] to be independent of the choice of the trivialization (e i (k)), determining uniquely KM ∈ Z 2 . It was rigorously shown in [CITATION_2] and in [CITATION_3] that KM is the only obstruction for trivializing the 2d TRI valence bundle with Kramers' pairs.",
